#META# writingSupportDetails: Fading/discolouration :: tears
#META# writingSupportNotes: Black ink, red (faded) embelishments, pasted onto a sheet
#META# contentSummary: The second section of a talismanic scroll containing the 99 names of God, an invocation against arrow shots, the khātam (Solomonic seal?), the Throne verse Q. 2:255, and Q. 2:256, and a selection of invocations for warding off various diseases. See "DOC 53" (section 1) & "DOC 52" (section 3).
